DataElement.preferredDefinition: A set of actions and observations, performed to verify or falsify a hypothesis or research a causal relationship between phenomena.:The property of being measured and described using two orthogonal directions.:A type of chromatography in which separation of a mixture is achieved by passing a sample in a stream of liquid solvent through some form of material that will provide resistance by virtue of chemical interactions between the components of the sample and the material.:Preceding all others in time or space or degree.:The magnitude of something in a particular direction, especially length or width or height.:A rule which guides how an activity should be performed._Brought into existence.:The particular day, month and year an event will happen or has happened._Generic value domain for a java datatype that represents a specific instant in time, with millisecond precision.
